00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:18,650
Scott: It kind of sucks.

668
00:39:19,771 --> 00:39:23,430
Scott: I mean, I use it, and it's getting better, but it still sucks in many ways.

669
00:39:23,953 --> 00:39:26,460
Scott: And a lot of times what happens is they add new services.

670
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:32,620
Scott: For example, they have Route 53, which is awesome DNS service, and there's no interface for it on the console.

671
00:39:32,641 --> 00:39:34,298
Scott: The only interface for it is the API.

672
00:39:34,379 --> 00:39:42,078
Scott: So you have to open up your whatever programming language you use, load up the API library, and that's the only way you can do anything with Route 53.

673
00:39:42,078 --> 00:39:43,854
Scott: Their DNS service is with the API.

674
00:39:44,521 --> 00:39:46,036
Scott: And a lot of the stuff is like that.

675
00:39:46,076 --> 00:39:51,170
Scott: They keep adding more stuff to the console, but they seem to put a lot of... They have a new service.

676
00:39:51,550 --> 00:39:53,897
Scott: They'll just put the service out there before it's in the console.

677
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:55,109
Scott: They have no problem with that.

678
00:39:55,490 --> 00:39:58,179
Scott: The console is like its own separate thing that goes at its own pace.

679
00:39:58,825 --> 00:40:02,196
Scott: And as a result, there's a lot of alternative GUIs.

