716
00:42:13,554 --> 00:42:14,550
Rym: It's kind of amazing.

717
00:42:15,034 --> 00:42:16,289
Scott: But Amazon doesn't do that.

718
00:42:16,572 --> 00:42:25,677
Scott: So if you're buying an EC2 machine, and it's running, and that particular physical machine that it is running on breaks, you'll actually go down.

719
00:42:26,322 --> 00:42:27,068
Scott: They'll let you know.

720
00:42:27,912 --> 00:42:34,507
