00:43:14,850 --> 00:43:17,030
Scott: ElastiCache, which is, here's a memcache server.

738
00:43:18,390 --> 00:43:29,350
Scott: Elastic Beanstalk is sort of this weird thing, which is if you write a Java application in a particular way, you can run it, instead of running it on machines, you can run it on Elastic Beanstalk.

739
00:43:29,873 --> 00:43:34,299
Scott: If you run it on the Elastic Beanstalk, it's one click and that's it.

740
00:43:34,340 --> 00:43:34,744
