00:43:49,999 --> 00:43:50,969
Scott: Back to a little tiny bean.

746
00:43:51,690 --> 00:43:51,832
Scott: Right?

747
00:43:51,893 --> 00:43:56,809
Scott: Just live, real time auto-scaling if you have the kind of application that can run on that.

748
00:43:57,310 --> 00:43:59,817
Scott: That's pretty great if you can have that kind of application.

749
00:44:00,019 --> 00:44:00,222
Rym: Yup.

750
00:44:00,788 --> 00:44:18,090
Rym: I guess in general, this whole cloud thing, especially with Amazon, my personal use of it is that if I need a server for testing, like I have an image or something, it's really easy to instantiate a bunch of whatever I need in a hurry and not have to physically rack them somewhere.

751
00:44:19,232 --> 00:44:24,530
